here i think the `Notifier` abstraction will come in handy, since there is no need to dispatch manually anymore.
conceptually the method will look something like this:

```python
notifiers = {
    "TopicConfigurations:" SnsNotifier(),
    "LambdaFunctionConfigurations": LambdaNotifier(),
    # ...
}

for type, notification_configs in notifications.items():
    for config in notification_configs:
        notifiers[type].notify(ctx, config) # <- this call should happen asynchronously, so we should add it to an executor queue, for example by using a ThreadPoolExecutor
```

The other question I have is why we have a separate module for this:
```go
func TestGenerateProgram(t *testing.T) {
   os.Chdir("../../../dotnet") // chdir into codegen/dotnet
   codegen.GenerateProgramBatchTest(t, test.ProgramTestBatch(1, 6))
