Also, I wonder if an iterator adapter could be a good solution here. Something to transform 

`Iterator<Item = SBP>` -> `Iterator<Item = Wrapper>`

```rust
enum Wrapper {
    Message(SBP),
    TimeChanged(GpsTime),
}
```

Whenever a message would change the current time, a `Wrapper::Time` is returned before that message. We could have one adapter for `MessageTime::Base` and one for `MessageTime::Rover`.  With an extension trait like 

```rust
trait SBPIterExt: Iterator<Item = SBP> {
    fn rover_time(self) -> RoverTimeIter;
    fn base_time(self) -> BaseTimeIter;
}
```
people can do `iter_messages(rdr).rover_time().etc()`. also could keep it simple and just expose the adapter it's like

```rust
let messages = iter_messages(rdr);
for _ in RoverTimeIter::new(messages) {}
```

Either way - the adapter seems useful for holding state like the running clock/reference time.

